This paper deals with graph clustering, which is a topic in computer science related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of modularity as a quality measure suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper proposes new algorithms for clustering, which may fall under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY) or numerical analysis (cs.NA).
